properties.name: A new beginning
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617Sparks, NVI moved to Sparks, NV to live with my dad and step mom when I was 9. All the sudden I had two brothers that I hardly knew instead of one I practically raised. Good times. lol The Bay City Rollers, Leif Garrett, and Shaun Cassidy were my true loves, and many unrequited crushes were had here.

properties.name: Electric Jesus
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 Alameda, CAMichael Garcia on vocals, Rich Williamson on guitars and arrangements, and Eric Matson on bass and drums. They have been playing great music together in various bands since the late 80\'s. Michael\'s enigmatic vocals, Rich\'s sizzling and amazing arrangements and guitar playing, and Eric\'s solid hot bass playing they put on a great show! You can purchase their CD\'s online and give em a listen on their MySpace page. Heavily influenced by their own idols, Led Zepplin, Red Lorry, Yellow Lorry, The Swans, Mission UK, and the Sisters of Mercy, their originals rock!

properties.name: Erin Shannon Mobile Massage *Women Only*
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 Fairfax, CA 94930Have a spa massage experience in the comfort of your own home. Erin has been doing Intuitive work, Hypnotherapy, and Bodywork for the last 15 years and can use her skills to create a deep nurturing, healing, and relaxing experience for you. Also available in a Fairfax location. Readings available in person, over the phone, or for your next party. Erin Shannon CMT 415-457-7242

properties.name: Grandma and Grandpa spoiling me rotten!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617Lake Almanor, CAI lived in a great house up at Lake Almanor till I was 6 years old and chased lizards and toads and swang on swings and played dress up. Good times.

properties.name: Great Jewelry and Knick Knacks!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 570 Castro Street, San Francisco, CA, 94114This is a great tiny place with some wonderful and interesting Estate Jewelry. If you are looking for something not neccessarily traditional as a gift and love Estate jewelry you will love this place. I can imagine that if I went in every day for a week I still wouldn\'t have seen everything.

properties.name: High School confidential chaos
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617   Carson City, NVAfter my 8th grade graduation, we moved to Carson City, I knew no one and started my freshmen year with all these kids that had been going to school their whole lives together. But what saved me? DRAMA class. What saved my grade average? DRAMA. lol I really enjoyed the shock value of being a weirdo at my high school and the joys of people, not quite understanding me. And my first job at a grocery store, good old Mayfair Market. So many back seats of cars, so little time. eeek.

properties.name: I don't remember living here
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617Seattle, WABut I remember watching Ed Sullivan and naming our new kitten after Sammy Davis Junior. And I remember moving away from here. I was three I think.

properties.name: I took my first steps here
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617Reno, NVAt what is now the Bicycle shop on Wells Avenue, or hopefully still the Bicycle shop, I took my first steps on the stage where my dads band played. I lived here till I was 1 1/2.

properties.name: I was born here :)
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617  Oakland, CAI lived on MacArthur Blvd, for my first 8 months of life in 1963-64.

properties.name: No Pie?
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617399 Grove Street, San Francisco, CA, 94102How can you trust a place to be nice and accomodating if they don\'t serve blessed Pie on a regular basis? Pie=Love Love=Pie

properties.name: Noodles!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie6171790 Haight St, San Francisco, CAI love this place, I had some citrus mint chicken noodles there last Tuesday that were divine. They had coriander in them too. The atmosphere can get a little loud but from what I could tell they have a great selection of neato drinkies on the menu and their food is clean and tasty.

properties.name: Queenie's Psychic Hit's for your next Party!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617  Fairfax, CAAdd some mystical fun to your next party! Queenie aka Erin has been doing psychic readings and medium work for the last 20 years and will add some extra oomph to your next get together. Using the Faeries Oracle or Tarot, and skills in spirit communication she can make your next event a memorable one for all your guests. Call for rates and availability. Also available for readings by phone or email. Queenie aka Erin 415-457-7242

properties.name: Rocks!  Beads!  Jewelry!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617213 Church Street, San Francisco CA This place has been one of my favorites for buying stones and beads for years. It has a nice cozy environment and a large selection of jewelry and beads. They have some amazing stone specimens to peruse and maybe purchase for your home. When I am in the City in this neighborhood I love dropping in there.

properties.name: Slick Willy
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617558 Castro Street, San Francisco CAI saw that, not only did he flick his butt on the ground and leave it burning, when you said something about it he did inch his foot on top of it as if to hide the evidence and there was a trash can less than a foot away. Weird.

properties.name: Sweetie Pies Glorious pies and treats!
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 Napa, CA520 Main Street Napa, CA 94559 707-257-8817 A wonderful place to get your sweet tooth on in Napa, CA. They also have soups, sandwiches and other delights there.

properties.name: Trees to climb and my brother Guy
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 Susanville, CA I lived in Susanville, when I was in 1st through 4th grade, I loved my brother Guy who was a toddler at the time. I climbed the oak tree next to my house and would sit at the top and listen to the world go by for hours. I loved to run away from home and hang out at the cemetary, it was quiet and pretty and I felt somehow comforted there.

properties.name: Walker's Pie Shoppe
properties.description: Posted by Queenie617 1491 Solano Ave, Albany, CA 94706A small unasuming diner with the best pie in the Bay Area! Nice large breakfasts too. But the PIE is DIVINE!
